# Motivation example: Why equal discrimination is unrealistic
cat("\n=== NİYƏ EQUAL DİSKRİMİNASİYA REALİSTİK DEYİL? ===\n")
## 
## === NİYƏ EQUAL DİSKRİMİNASİYA REALİSTİK DEYİL? ===
# Simulate realistic test scenarios
set.seed(2025)
realistic_scenarios <- list(
  math_test = list(
    items = c("2+3=?", "Basic algebra", "Geometry", "Calculus", "Advanced proofs"),
    expected_disc = c(0.8, 1.2, 1.5, 1.8, 1.0),
    reasoning = "Basic items less discriminating"
  ),
  
  reading_test = list(
    items = c("Word recognition", "Simple comprehension", "Inference", 
              "Critical analysis", "Literary interpretation"),
    expected_disc = c(0.9, 1.1, 1.6, 1.9, 1.4),
    reasoning = "Higher-order skills more discriminating"
  ),
  
  personality_scale = list(
    items = c("I like parties", "I am outgoing", "I enjoy socializing", 
              "I feel comfortable in groups", "I am the life of the party"),
    expected_disc = c(1.0, 1.5, 1.2, 1.3, 1.8),
    reasoning = "Some behaviors more indicative"
  )
)

for(scenario_name in names(realistic_scenarios)) {
  scenario <- realistic_scenarios[[scenario_name]]
  cat(toupper(scenario_name), ":\n")
  cat("Reasoning:", scenario$reasoning, "\n")
  
  scenario_df <- data.frame(
    Item = scenario$items,
    Expected_a = scenario$expected_disc,
    Interpretation = ifelse(scenario$expected_disc < 1.0, "Weak discriminator",
                           ifelse(scenario$expected_disc < 1.5, "Moderate discriminator",
                                 "Strong discriminator"))
  )
  
  print(scenario_df)
  cat("\n")
}

2.2 2PL Modelinin Riyazi İfadəsi

cat("=== 2PL MODELİNİN RİYAZİ İFADƏSİ ===\n\n")
## === 2PL MODELİNİN RİYAZİ İFADƏSİ ===
cat("1. Əsas 2PL Tənliyi:\n")
## 1. Əsas 2PL Tənliyi:
cat("P(Xᵢ = 1 | θ, aᵢ, bᵢ) = exp[aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)] / (1 + exp[aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)])\n\n")
## P(Xᵢ = 1 | θ, aᵢ, bᵢ) = exp[aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)] / (1 + exp[aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)])
cat("Parametr Təfərrüatları:\n")
## Parametr Təfərrüatları:
parameter_details <- data.frame(
  Parametr = c("θ (theta)", "aᵢ (alpha)", "bᵢ (beta)", "Xᵢ"),
  
  Adı = c("Person ability", "Item discrimination", "Item difficulty", "Response"),
  
  Vahid = c("Logit", "Logit/logit", "Logit", "Binary (0/1)"),
  
  Aralıq = c("-∞ to +∞", "0 to +∞", "-∞ to +∞", "0 or 1"),
  
  Tipik_Dəyər = c("-3 to +3", "0.5 to 3.0", "-3 to +3", "0 or 1"),
  
  İnterpretasiya = c("Higher = more able", "Higher = better discriminator", 
                     "Higher = more difficult", "1 = correct response")
)

print(parameter_details)
##     Parametr                 Adı        Vahid   Aralıq Tipik_Dəyər
## 1  θ (theta)      Person ability        Logit -∞ to +∞    -3 to +3
## 2 aᵢ (alpha) Item discrimination  Logit/logit  0 to +∞  0.5 to 3.0
## 3  bᵢ (beta)     Item difficulty        Logit -∞ to +∞    -3 to +3
## 4         Xᵢ            Response Binary (0/1)   0 or 1      0 or 1
##                  İnterpretasiya
## 1            Higher = more able
## 2 Higher = better discriminator
## 3       Higher = more difficult
## 4          1 = correct response
cat("\n2. Logit Forması:\n")
## 
## 2. Logit Forması:
cat("logit[P(Xᵢ = 1)] = aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)\n\n")
## logit[P(Xᵢ = 1)] = aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)
cat("3. Odds Forması:\n")
## 3. Odds Forması:
cat("odds[P(Xᵢ = 1)] = exp[aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)]\n\n")
## odds[P(Xᵢ = 1)] = exp[aᵢ(θ - bᵢ)]
# Numerical examples with different discrimination values
cat("Numerical Nümunələr (θ = 0, bᵢ = 0, müxtəlif aᵢ):\n")
## Numerical Nümunələr (θ = 0, bᵢ = 0, müxtəlif aᵢ):
discrimination_values <- c(0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5)
probabilities_at_theta0 <- prob_2pl(0, discrimination_values, 0)

discrimination_examples <- data.frame(
  Discrimination_a = discrimination_values,
  Probability = round(probabilities_at_theta0, 3),
  Interpretation = c("Weak discrimination", "Moderate (Rasch-like)", 
                     "Good discrimination", "Strong discrimination", 
                     "Very strong discrimination"),
  Practical_Meaning = c("Flat ICC", "Standard slope", "Steep ICC", 
                        "Very steep ICC", "Nearly step function")
)

print(discrimination_examples)

## 3              1.5         0.5        Good discrimination            Steep ICC

# Effect of discrimination on probability differences
cat("\nDiskriminasiya Təsiri (θ = ±1, bᵢ = 0):\n")
## 
## Diskriminasiya Təsiri (θ = ±1, bᵢ = 0):
theta_values <- c(-1, 0, 1)
disc_effect_results <- data.frame(
  Discrimination = rep(discrimination_values, each = 3),
  Theta = rep(theta_values, length(discrimination_values)),
  Probability = round(as.vector(sapply(discrimination_values, function(a) 
    prob_2pl(theta_values, a, 0))), 3)
)

# Reshape for better display
library(dplyr)
disc_effect_wide <- disc_effect_results %>%
  tidyr::pivot_wider(names_from = Theta, values_from = Probability, 
                     names_prefix = "theta_")

if(ncol(disc_effect_wide) >= 4) {
  disc_effect_wide$Difference <- disc_effect_wide$theta_1 - disc_effect_wide$`theta_-1`
  print(disc_effect_wide)
  
  cat("\nKey Insight: Yüksək discrimination → θ səviyyələri arasında böyük fərq\n")
}

3 Item Discrimination Parametri

3.1 Discrimination Parametrinin Təsiri

cat("=== İTEM DİSKRİMİNASİYA PARAMETRİ ===\n\n")
## === İTEM DİSKRİMİNASİYA PARAMETRİ ===
cat("Discrimination Parametrinin ICC-yə Təsiri:\n\n")
## Discrimination Parametrinin ICC-yə Təsiri:
# Create ICC comparison with different discriminations
theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.1)
difficulty <- 0  # Fixed difficulty for comparison
discriminations <- c(0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5)
colors <- c("red", "orange", "blue", "purple", "darkgreen")

plot(theta_range, prob_2pl(theta_range, 1.0, difficulty), 
     type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
     main = "Discrimination Parametrinin ICC-yə Təsiri (b = 0)",
     xlab = "Theta (θ)", ylab = "P(X = 1 | θ)",
     ylim = c(0, 1), xlim = c(-4, 4))

for(i in 1:length(discriminations)) {
  prob <- prob_2pl(theta_range, discriminations[i], difficulty)
  lines(theta_range, prob, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
}

abline(h = 0.5, lty = 2, col = "gray", lwd = 2)
abline(v = difficulty, lty = 2, col = "gray", lwd = 2)

legend("right", paste0("a = ", discriminations), 
       col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.9)

grid(TRUE)

cat("ICC Xüsusiyyətləri:\n")
## ICC Xüsusiyyətləri:

  Discrimination_a = discriminations,
  
  Slope_at_b = round(discriminations / 4, 3),  # Maximum slope = a/4
  
  Range_80pct = round(4 / discriminations, 2),  # Approximate θ range for 10%-90%
  
  Steepness = c("Very gradual", "Gradual", "Moderate", "Steep", "Very steep"),
  
  Practical_Use = c("Screening", "General assessment", "Good discrimination", 
                    "High-stakes testing", "Precise measurement")
)

3.2 Discrimination və Information Functions

cat("=== DİSKRİMİNASİYA VƏ INFORMATION FUNCTİONS ===\n\n")
## === DİSKRİMİNASİYA VƏ INFORMATION FUNCTİONS ===
cat("Item Information Function (IIF):\n")
## Item Information Function (IIF):
cat("I(θ) = a²ᵢ × P(θ) × [1 - P(θ)]\n\n")
## I(θ) = a²ᵢ × P(θ) × [1 - P(θ)]
# Calculate and plot information functions
theta_range <- seq(-4, 4, by = 0.1)
difficulty <- 0
discriminations <- c(0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 2.5)

# Information function plot
plot(theta_range, info_2pl(theta_range, 1.0, difficulty),
     type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "blue",
     main = "Item Information Functions (b = 0)",
     xlab = "Theta (θ)", ylab = "Information I(θ)",
     ylim = c(0, 1.6))

colors <- c("red", "orange", "blue", "purple", "darkgreen")
for(i in 1:length(discriminations)) {
  info <- info_2pl(theta_range, discriminations[i], difficulty)
  lines(theta_range, info, lwd = 3, col = colors[i])
}

abline(v = difficulty, lty = 2, col = "gray")
legend("topright", paste0("a = ", discriminations), 
       col = colors, lwd = 3, cex = 0.9)

grid(TRUE)

cat("Information Function Xüsusiyyətləri:\n")
## Information Function Xüsusiyyətləri:
# Calculate peak information for each discrimination
peak_info <- discriminations^2 / 4  # Maximum value at θ = b

info_characteristics <- data.frame(
  Discrimination = discriminations,
  
  Peak_Information = round(peak_info, 3),
  
  Peak_Location = rep(difficulty, length(discriminations)),  # Always at b
  
  Information_at_theta_1 = round(sapply(discriminations, function(a) 
    info_2pl(1, a, difficulty)), 3),
  
  SE_at_Peak = round(1 / sqrt(peak_info), 3),
  
  Relative_Efficiency = round(peak_info / peak_info[2], 2)  # Relative to a=1
)

print(info_characteristics)
##   Discrimination Peak_Information Peak_Location Information_at_theta_1
## 1            0.5            0.062             0                  0.059
## 2            1.0            0.250             0                  0.197
## 3            1.5            0.562             0                  0.336
## 4            2.0            1.000             0                  0.420
## 5            2.5            1.562             0                  0.438
##   SE_at_Peak Relative_Efficiency
## 1      4.000                0.25
## 2      2.000                1.00

## 5      0.800                6.25

# Test Information Function concept
cat("\n=== TEST INFORMATION FUNCTION ===\n")
## 
## === TEST INFORMATION FUNCTION ===
cat("Test Information = Σ Item Information\n")
## Test Information = Σ Item Information
cat("TIF(θ) = Σᵢ Iᵢ(θ) = Σᵢ a²ᵢ × Pᵢ(θ) × [1 - Pᵢ(θ)]\n\n")
## TIF(θ) = Σᵢ Iᵢ(θ) = Σᵢ a²ᵢ × Pᵢ(θ) × [1 - Pᵢ(θ)]
# Example: Test with mixed discrimination items
mixed_discriminations <- c(0.8, 1.2, 1.5, 1.8, 1.0, 1.3, 1.6, 0.9, 1.4, 1.1)
mixed_difficulties <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = 10)

# Calculate test information
test_info <- numeric(length(theta_range))
for(i in 1:length(mixed_discriminations)) {
  item_info <- info_2pl(theta_range, mixed_discriminations[i], mixed_difficulties[i])
  test_info <- test_info + item_info
}

# Plot test information
plot(theta_range, test_info, type = "l", lwd = 3, col = "darkblue",
     main = "Test Information Function (10 items)",
     xlab = "Theta (θ)", ylab = "Test Information",
     ylim = c(0, max(test_info) * 1.1))

# Add individual item contributions (first 3 items)
for(i in 1:3) {
  item_info <- info_2pl(theta_range, mixed_discriminations[i], mixed_difficulties[i])
  lines(theta_range, item_info, lty = 2, col = colors[i])
}

grid(TRUE)
legend("topright", c("Test Information", "Item 1", "Item 2", "Item 3"),
       lwd = c(3, 1, 1, 1), lty = c(1, 2, 2, 2),
       col = c("darkblue", colors[1:3]), cex = 0.8)

# Test-level statistics
cat("\nTest-Level Information Statistikaları:\n")
## 
## Test-Level Information Statistikaları:

# Practical simulation: Model comparison
cat("\n=== PRAKTİK SİMULYASİYA: MODEL MÜQAYİSƏ ===\n")
## 
## === PRAKTİK SİMULYASİYA: MODEL MÜQAYİSƏ ===
simulate_model_comparison <- function() {
  set.seed(54321)
  
  n_persons <- 600
  n_items <- 15
  
  # Scenario 1: True Rasch data (equal discrimination)
  theta_rasch <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)
  disc_rasch <- rep(1.0, n_items)  # Equal discrimination
  diff_rasch <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  data_rasch <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- prob_2pl(theta_rasch[i], disc_rasch[j], diff_rasch[j])
      data_rasch[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  # Scenario 2: True 2PL data (variable discrimination)
  theta_2pl <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)
  disc_2pl <- runif(n_items, 0.6, 2.4)  # Variable discrimination
  diff_2pl <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  data_2pl <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- prob_2pl(theta_2pl[i], disc_2pl[j], diff_2pl[j])
      data_2pl[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  return(list(
    rasch_scenario = list(data = data_rasch, true_disc = disc_rasch),
    twopl_scenario = list(data = data_2pl, true_disc = disc_2pl)
  ))
}

comparison_data <- simulate_model_comparison()

5 R-də 2PL Analizi: ltm Paketi

5.1 ltm Paketi ilə Comprehensive 2PL Analysis

cat("=== R-DƏ 2PL ANALİZİ: ltm PAKETİ ===\n\n")
## === R-DƏ 2PL ANALİZİ: ltm PAKETİ ===
# ltm paketi ilə 2PL analizi
perform_ltm_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== ltm 2PL ANALİZİ:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(ltm, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("ltm paketi mövcud deyil. Manual analiz aparılır.\n")
    return(perform_manual_2pl_analysis(data, data_name))
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    # 1. Fit 1PL (Rasch) model
    cat("1. Rasch (1PL) Model fitting...\n")
    model_1pl <- rasch(data, constraint = cbind(1:ncol(data), 1))
    
    # 2. Fit 2PL model
    cat("2. 2PL Model fitting...\n")
    model_2pl <- ltm(data ~ z1)
    
    # 3. Model comparison
    cat("\n=== MODEL MÜQAYİSƏ ===\n")
    
    aic_1pl <- AIC(model_1pl)
    aic_2pl <- AIC(model_2pl)
    bic_1pl <- BIC(model_1pl)
    bic_2pl <- BIC(model_2pl)
    
    loglik_1pl <- logLik(model_1pl)
    loglik_2pl <- logLik(model_2pl)
    
    cat("1PL (Rasch) Model:\n")
    cat("  Log-Likelihood:", round(as.numeric(loglik_1pl), 2), "\n")
    cat("  AIC:", round(aic_1pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("  BIC:", round(bic_1pl, 2), "\n")
    
    cat("2PL Model:\n")
    cat("  Log-Likelihood:", round(as.numeric(loglik_2pl), 2), "\n")
    cat("  AIC:", round(aic_2pl, 2), "\n")
    cat("  BIC:", round(bic_2pl, 2), "\n")
    
    # Likelihood ratio test
    lr_statistic <- 2 * (as.numeric(loglik_2pl) - as.numeric(loglik_1pl))
    df_diff <- attr(loglik_2pl, "df") - attr(loglik_1pl, "df")
    lr_p_value <- 1 - pchisq(lr_statistic, df_diff)
    
    cat("\nLikelihood Ratio Test (2PL vs 1PL):\n")
    cat("  LR statistic:", round(lr_statistic, 2), "\n")
    cat("  df:", df_diff, "\n")
    cat("  p-value:", ifelse(lr_p_value < 0.001, "<0.001", round(lr_p_value, 4)), "\n")
    
    # Model selection
    if(lr_p_value < 0.05) {
      cat("  → 2PL significantly better than 1PL\n")
      preferred_model <- model_2pl
      preferred_name <- "2PL"
    } else {
      cat("  → 1PL adequate (parsimony preferred)\n")
      preferred_model <- model_1pl
      preferred_name <- "1PL"
    }
    
    cat("\nPreferred model:", preferred_name, "\n\n")
    
    # 4. Item parameters (2PL model)
    cat("=== 2PL İTEM PARAMETRLƏRİ ===\n")
    
    params_2pl <- coef(model_2pl)
    discrimination <- params_2pl[, 1]
    difficulty <- -params_2pl[, 2] / params_2pl[, 1]  # Convert to IRT parameterization
    
    item_params_table <- data.frame(
      Item = 1:ncol(data),
      Discrimination = round(discrimination, 3),
      Difficulty = round(difficulty, 3),
      Quality = ifelse(discrimination < 0.5, "Poor",
                      ifelse(discrimination < 1.0, "Fair",
                            ifelse(discrimination < 1.5, "Good",
                                  ifelse(discrimination < 2.0, "Very Good", "Excellent")))),
      Interpretation = ifelse(difficulty < -1, "Easy",
                             ifelse(difficulty < 0, "Moderate-Easy",
                                   ifelse(difficulty < 1, "Moderate-Hard", "Hard")))
    )
    
    print(head(item_params_table, 10))
    
    # 5. Item and Test Information
    cat("\n=== INFORMATION FUNCTİONS ===\n")
    
    # Item information at different theta levels
    theta_levels <- c(-2, -1, 0, 1, 2)
    
    cat("Item Information at Different θ Levels:\n")
    item_info_matrix <- matrix(NA, nrow = min(5, ncol(data)), ncol = length(theta_levels))
    
    for(i in 1:min(5, ncol(data))) {
      for(j in 1:length(theta_levels)) {
        item_info_matrix[i, j] <- info_2pl(theta_levels[j], 
                                          discrimination[i], difficulty[i])
      }
    }
    
    colnames(item_info_matrix) <- paste0("theta_", theta_levels)
    rownames(item_info_matrix) <- paste0("Item_", 1:nrow(item_info_matrix))
    print(round(item_info_matrix, 3))
    
    # Test information
    test_info_levels <- numeric(length(theta_levels))
    for(j in 1:length(theta_levels)) {
      test_info_levels[j] <- sum(sapply(1:ncol(data), function(i) 
        info_2pl(theta_levels[j], discrimination[i], difficulty[i])))
    }
    
    cat("\nTest Information Function:\n")
    test_info_table <- data.frame(
      Theta = theta_levels,
      Test_Information = round(test_info_levels, 2),
      Standard_Error = round(1 / sqrt(test_info_levels), 3),
      Reliability = round(1 - (1 / test_info_levels), 3)
    )
    
    print(test_info_table)
    
    # 6. Item and person fit
    cat("\n=== FIT STATİSTİKLƏRİ ===\n")
    
    # Item fit
    tryCatch({
      item_fit <- item.fit(model_2pl)
      if(!is.null(item_fit)) {
        cat("Item Fit (first 5 items):\n")
        print(head(item_fit, 5))
        
        misfit_items <- sum(item_fit$p.value < 0.05, na.rm = TRUE)
        cat("Misfitting items (p < 0.05):", misfit_items, "/", ncol(data), "\n")
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Item fit hesablanmadı\n")
    })
    
    # Person fit
    tryCatch({
      person_fit <- person.fit(model_2pl)
      if(!is.null(person_fit)) {
        misfit_persons <- sum(person_fit$p.values < 0.05, na.rm = TRUE)
        total_persons <- length(person_fit$p.values)
        misfit_rate <- round(100 * misfit_persons / total_persons, 1)
        
        cat("Person fit: ", misfit_persons, "/", total_persons, 
            " (", misfit_rate, "%) misfitting\n")
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Person fit hesablanmadı\n")
    })
    
    # 7. Plots
    cat("\n=== GRAFİK TƏQDİMATLAR ===\n")
    
    # ICC plots
    tryCatch({
      plot(model_2pl, type = "ICC", items = 1:min(6, ncol(data)),
           main = paste("ICCs -", data_name))
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("ICC plots çəkilmədi\n")
    })
    
    # Information plot
    tryCatch({
      plot(model_2pl, type = "IIC", items = 1:min(6, ncol(data)),
           main = paste("Item Information -", data_name))
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Information plots çəkilmədi\n")
    })
    
    return(list(
      model_1pl = model_1pl,
      model_2pl = model_2pl,
      preferred_model = preferred_name,
      discrimination = discrimination,
      difficulty = difficulty,
      lr_test = list(statistic = lr_statistic, p_value = lr_p_value)
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("ltm analysis xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(perform_manual_2pl_analysis(data, data_name))
  })
}

# Manual 2PL analysis (ltm olmayanda)
perform_manual_2pl_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MANUAL 2PL ANALİZİ:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  # Basic statistics
  n_persons <- nrow(data)
  n_items <- ncol(data)
  
  cat("Data Information:\n")
  cat("Persons:", n_persons, "\n")
  cat("Items:", n_items, "\n")
  
  # Simple discrimination estimates using item-total correlations
  total_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  discrimination_proxy <- numeric(n_items)
  difficulty_proxy <- numeric(n_items)
  
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    # Item-total correlation as discrimination proxy
    rest_total <- total_scores - data[, j]
    discrimination_proxy[j] <- cor(data[, j], rest_total, use = "complete.obs")
    
    # Item mean as difficulty proxy
    item_prop <- mean(data[, j], na.rm = TRUE)
    difficulty_proxy[j] <- -qlogis(pmax(0.01, pmin(0.99, item_prop)))
  }
  
  cat("\nEstimated Item Properties:\n")
  manual_params <- data.frame(
    Item = 1:n_items,
    Disc_Proxy = round(discrimination_proxy, 3),
    Diff_Proxy = round(difficulty_proxy, 3),
    Quality = ifelse(discrimination_proxy < 0.2, "Poor",
                    ifelse(discrimination_proxy < 0.4, "Fair", "Good"))
  )
  
  print(head(manual_params, 10))
  
  return(list(
    discrimination_proxy = discrimination_proxy,
    difficulty_proxy = difficulty_proxy
  ))
}

## 
## === MİRT PAKETİ İLƏ ADVANCED 2PL ANALİZİ ===
# mirt paketi ilə analiz
perform_mirt_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MIRT 2PL ANALİZİ:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(mirt, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("mirt paketi mövcud deyil.\n")
    return(NULL)
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    # 1. Fit 1PL model
    cat("1. 1PL Model (Rasch) fitting...\n")
    model_1pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "Rasch", verbose = FALSE)
    
    # 2. Fit 2PL model
    cat("2. 2PL Model fitting...\n")
    model_2pl_mirt <- mirt(data, 1, itemtype = "2PL", verbose = FALSE)
    
    # 3. Model comparison
    cat("\n=== MIRT MODEL MÜQAYİSƏ ===\n")
    
    # Extract fit indices
    fit_1pl <- extract.mirt(model_1pl_mirt, "fit")
    fit_2pl <- extract.mirt(model_2pl_mirt, "fit")
    
    cat("1PL Model Fit Indices:\n")
    cat("  AIC:", round(fit_1pl["AIC"], 2), "\n")
    cat("  BIC:", round(fit_1pl["BIC"], 2), "\n")
    cat("  Log-likelihood:", round(fit_1pl["logLik"], 2), "\n")
    
    cat("2PL Model Fit Indices:\n")
    cat("  AIC:", round(fit_2pl["AIC"], 2), "\n")
    cat("  BIC:", round(fit_2pl["BIC"], 2), "\n")
    cat("  Log-likelihood:", round(fit_2pl["logLik"], 2), "\n")
    
    # Model comparison test
    model_comparison <- anova(model_1pl_mirt, model_2pl_mirt)
    cat("\nModel Comparison (ANOVA):\n")
    print(model_comparison)
    
    # 4. Item parameters
    cat("\n=== İTEM PARAMETRLƏRİ ===\n")
    
    params_1pl <- coef(model_1pl_mirt, simplify = TRUE)
    params_2pl <- coef(model_2pl_mirt, simplify = TRUE)
    
    cat("2PL Item Parameters:\n")
    item_params_mirt <- params_2pl$items
    
    mirt_params_table <- data.frame(
      Item = 1:nrow(item_params_mirt),
      Discrimination = round(item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3),
      Difficulty = round(item_params_mirt[, "d"] / -item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3),
      SE_Disc = round(params_2pl$SEitems[, "a1"], 3),
      SE_Diff = round(params_2pl$SEitems[, "d"] / item_params_mirt[, "a1"], 3)
    )
    
    print(head(mirt_params_table, 10))
    
    # 5. Item and Test Information
    cat("\n=== INFORMATION ANALİZİ ===\n")
    
    # Extract information
    theta_seq <- seq(-3, 3, by = 0.5)
    
    # Test information
    test_info_mirt <- testinfo(model_2pl_mirt, theta_seq)
    
    cat("Test Information at Different θ Levels:\n")
    info_table_mirt <- data.frame(
      Theta = theta_seq,
      Test_Info = round(test_info_mirt, 2),
      SE = round(1 / sqrt(test_info_mirt), 3),
      Reliability = round(1 - 1/test_info_mirt, 3)
    )
    
    print(head(info_table_mirt, 7))
    
    # 6. Person parameters
    cat("\n=== PERSON PARAMETRLƏRİ ===\n")
    
    # Factor scores (EAP estimates)
    person_scores <- fscores(model_2pl_mirt, method = "EAP")
    
    cat("Person Ability Estimates (first 10):\n")
    person_summary_mirt <- data.frame(
      Person = 1:min(10, nrow(person_scores)),
      Raw_Score = rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)[1:min(10, nrow(data))],
      EAP_Theta = round(person_scores[1:min(10, nrow(person_scores)), 1], 3),
      SE_Theta = round(person_scores[1:min(10, nrow(person_scores)), 2], 3)
    )
    
    print(person_summary_mirt)
    
    # 7. Model fit diagnostics
    cat("\n=== MODEL FIT DİAGNOSTİKS ===\n")
    
    # Item fit
    tryCatch({
      item_fit_mirt <- itemfit(model_2pl_mirt)
      if(!is.null(item_fit_mirt)) {
        cat("Item Fit Statistics (S-X² method):\n")
        fit_summary_mirt <- data.frame(
          Item = 1:nrow(item_fit_mirt),
          S_X2 = round(item_fit_mirt[, "S_X2"], 2),
          df = item_fit_mirt[, "df"],
          p_value = round(item_fit_mirt[, "p.S_X2"], 4),
          Fit_Status = ifelse(item_fit_mirt[, "p.S_X2"] < 0.05, "Misfit", "Fit")
        )
        
        print(head(fit_summary_mirt, 10))
        
        misfit_count <- sum(item_fit_mirt[, "p.S_X2"] < 0.05, na.rm = TRUE)
        cat("Misfitting items:", misfit_count, "/", nrow(item_fit_mirt), "\n")
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Item fit hesablanmadı:", e$message, "\n")
    })
    
    # Person fit
    tryCatch({
      person_fit_mirt <- personfit(model_2pl_mirt)
      if(!is.null(person_fit_mirt)) {
        misfit_persons_mirt <- sum(person_fit_mirt[, "p.Zh"] < 0.05, na.rm = TRUE)
        total_persons_mirt <- sum(!is.na(person_fit_mirt[, "p.Zh"]))
        
        cat("Person fit: ", misfit_persons_mirt, "/", total_persons_mirt, 
            " misfitting\n")
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Person fit hesablanmadı:", e$message, "\n")
    })
    
    # 8. Residual analysis
    cat("\n=== RESİDUAL ANALİZİ ===\n")
    
    tryCatch({
      residuals_mirt <- residuals(model_2pl_mirt, type = "Q3")
      if(!is.null(residuals_mirt)) {
        q3_values <- residuals_mirt[upper.tri(residuals_mirt)]
        
        cat("Q3 Residual Statistics:\n")
        cat("  Mean Q3:", round(mean(q3_values, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
        cat("  Max |Q3|:", round(max(abs(q3_values), na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
        cat("  Q3 > 0.20:", sum(abs(q3_values) > 0.20, na.rm = TRUE), "pairs\n")
      }
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Residual analysis aparılmadı:", e$message, "\n")
    })
    
    return(list(
      model_1pl = model_1pl_mirt,
      model_2pl = model_2pl_mirt,
      item_params = mirt_params_table,
      person_scores = person_scores,
      test_info = test_info_mirt
    ))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("mirt analysis xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# MIRT analizi
mirt_result <- perform_mirt_analysis(comparison_data$twopl_scenario$data, "2PL Scenario")

    cat("\n=== LTM vs MIRT PARAMETER MÜQAYİSƏ ===\n")
    
    n_compare <- min(length(ltm_result$discrimination), 
                     nrow(mirt_result$item_params), 10)
    
    parameter_comparison <- data.frame(
      Item = 1:n_compare,
      LTM_Disc = round(ltm_result$discrimination[1:n_compare], 3),
      MIRT_Disc = round(mirt_result$item_params$Discrimination[1:n_compare], 3),
      LTM_Diff = round(ltm_result$difficulty[1:n_compare], 3),
      MIRT_Diff = round(mirt_result$item_params$Difficulty[1:n_compare], 3)
    )
    
    print(parameter_comparison)
    
    # Correlations
    cor_disc <- cor(ltm_result$discrimination[1:n_compare], 
                    mirt_result$item_params$Discrimination[1:n_compare])
    cor_diff <- cor(ltm_result$difficulty[1:n_compare], 
                    mirt_result$item_params$Difficulty[1:n_compare])
    
    cat("\nParameter Correlations (ltm vs mirt):\n")
    cat("Discrimination:", round(cor_disc, 3), "\n")
    cat("Difficulty:", round(cor_diff, 3), "\n")
  }
}

# Demonstrate estimation sensitivity
cat("\n=== ESTİMATİON SENSİTİVİTY DEMONSTRASİYA ===\n")
## 
## === ESTİMATİON SENSİTİVİTY DEMONSTRASİYA ===
demonstrate_estimation_sensitivity <- function() {
  # Use the 2PL scenario data
  data <- comparison_data$twopl_scenario$data
  
  cat("Estimation Sensitivity Analysis:\n")
  cat("Data: 2PL scenario (", nrow(data), "x", ncol(data), ")\n\n")
  
  # Different sample sizes
  sample_sizes <- c(200, 400, 600, 800)
  
  estimation_results <- data.frame(
    Sample_Size = integer(),
    Mean_Disc_Est = numeric(),
    SD_Disc_Est = numeric(),
    Mean_Diff_Est = numeric(),
    SD_Diff_Est = numeric(),
    Estimation_Quality = character()
  )
  
  for(n in sample_sizes) {
    cat("Sample size:", n, "\n")
    
    # Subsample data
    indices <- sample(1:nrow(data), min(n, nrow(data)))
    sub_data <- data[indices, ]
    
    # Simple estimation using item-total correlations
    total_scores <- rowSums(sub_data, na.rm = TRUE)
    
    disc_estimates <- numeric(ncol(sub_data))
    diff_estimates <- numeric(ncol(sub_data))
    
    for(j in 1:ncol(sub_data)) {
      rest_total <- total_scores - sub_data[, j]
      disc_estimates[j] <- cor(sub_data[, j], rest_total, use = "complete.obs")
      
      item_prop <- mean(sub_data[, j], na.rm = TRUE)
      diff_estimates[j] <- -qlogis(pmax(0.01, pmin(0.99, item_prop)))
    }
    
    # Remove any NA values
    valid_disc <- disc_estimates[!is.na(disc_estimates)]
    valid_diff <- diff_estimates[!is.na(diff_estimates)]
    
    if(length(valid_disc) > 0 && length(valid_diff) > 0) {
      mean_disc <- mean(valid_disc)
      sd_disc <- sd(valid_disc)
      mean_diff <- mean(valid_diff)
      sd_diff <- sd(valid_diff)
      
      # Quality assessment
      if(sd_disc < 0.2 && sd_diff < 1.0) {
        quality <- "Good"
      } else if(sd_disc < 0.3 && sd_diff < 1.5) {
        quality <- "Fair"
      } else {
        quality <- "Poor"
      }
      
      estimation_results <- rbind(estimation_results, data.frame(
        Sample_Size = n,
        Mean_Disc_Est = round(mean_disc, 3),
        SD_Disc_Est = round(sd_disc, 3),
        Mean_Diff_Est = round(mean_diff, 3),
        SD_Diff_Est = round(sd_diff, 3),
        Estimation_Quality = quality
      ))
    }
  }
  
  cat("\nEstimation Results by Sample Size:\n")
  print(estimation_results)
  
  return(estimation_results)
}
